            "summary": "According to a report from Google Threat Intelligence, the threat group COLDRIVER is utilizing a new malware named LOSTKEYS to steal documents from Western targets. The malware signifies the group's transition from credential phishing to more sophisticated attacks and is installed in four steps involving a lure website, a PowerShell script, device evasion, and payload retrieval. LOSTKEYS can steal files from directories and extensions, extract system information, and send data to COLDRIVER. Google has taken measures to address the threat, adding malicious websites to its \"Safe Browsing\" feature. COLDRIVER, a Russian-backed group, targets high-profile Western individuals such as diplomats and journalists. In a related trend, crypto hack losses hit $2 billion in the first quarter of 2025, surpassing all losses from 2024. Major vulnerabilities include operational flaws and weak access controls, with attackers increasingly using social engineering tactics. Noteworthy was the $1.5 billion hack on cryptocurrency exchange Bybit by the Lazarus Group in February.",
